    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e24e46b5d2bea448",
      "text": "Netlify offers the option to handle DNS management for you. This enables advanced subdomain automation and deployment features, and ensures that your site uses our CDN for the root domain as well as for subdomains like www - [https://www.netlify.com/docs/custom-domains/#automatic netlify.com]\n\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "3bc8a10a67d2cb3e",
      "text": "After adding a custom domain to your site in the Custom domains panel, click the options button represented with a … icon next to your primary domain, and select Set up Netlify DNS in the dropdown. This will open a 3-step flow to move your DNS traffic to Netlify:\n\n1. Confirm that you want to add your domain to Netlify by creating a DNS zone for the domain – the DNS zone will contain all of the DNS records for that domain. This step won’t change how we serve your site. Your DNS traffic will only be served by Netlify once you complete all 3 steps.\n\n2. Netlify will create the DNS records required for your Netlify site automatically. We are happy to support DNS for all records in your domain including ones that don’t point to our service; if you’re using your domain for other services, like email, you will need to add all other records like MX, etc, in this step.\n\n3. Make note of the four nameservers assigned to your new DNS zone – they may vary for every DNS zone you create. Go to your domain registrar and change your nameservers to point at your new Netlify DNS zone.\n"
    },
